In [6]:
smiles = ['c1cccc(O)c1', 'c1c(O)ccc(O)c1','c1(O)cc(c2ccccc2)cc(O)c1']
mols= []
images =[]

for s in smiles:
    m = oddt.toolkit.readstring('smi', s)
    if not m.OBMol.Has3D(): 
        m.make3D(forcefield='mmff94', steps=150)
        m.removeh()
        m.OBMol.AddPolarHydrogens()

    mols.append(m)
    ###with print m.OBMol.Has3D() was found that:
    ### deep copy needed to keep 3D , write svg make mols flat
    images.append((SVG(copy.deepcopy(m).write('svg'))))

display_svg(*images)

  • --cpu -

from rdkit import Chem
from rdkit.Chem import AllChem
nag = Chem.MolFromSmiles('CC(=O)NC1C(C(C(OC1O)CO)O)O')
AllChem.Compute2DCoords(nag)
display(nag)

Canonical SMILE

  • OH: OC(=O)NC1C(C(C(OC1O)CO)O)O
  • NH3+: [NH3+]C(=O)NC1C(C(C(OC1O)CO)O)O
  • H: C(=O)NC1C(C(C(OC1O)CO)O)O
  • Ph: C1=CC=[C]C=C1C(=O)NC1C(C(C(OC1O)CO)O)O
  • COO-: [O-]C(=O)C(=O)NC1C(C(C(OC1O)CO)O)O

import pandas as pd

translate = {
    "C7H13NO7": "OH",
    "C7H15N2O6": "NH3+",
    "C7H13NO6": "H",
    "C13H17NO6": "Ph",
    "C8H13NO8": "COO-"
}

formulas = [x.formula for x in res]
ligands = [translate[x] for x in formulas]
affinities = [x.data["vina_affinity"] for x in res]
rmsd = [x.data["vina_rmsd_ub"] for x in res]
names = [x.residues[0].name for x in res]

df = pd.DataFrame(
    {
        "formula": formulas,
        "affinity": affinities,
        "rmsd": rmsd,
        "name": names,
        "ligand": ligands
    })
df = df.sort_values(by=['affinity'], ascending=[1])
df
